{"body": "**Reliability Issue: Missing Error Handling**

The `todoStore.create()` call is not wrapped in a try-catch block. If the store method throws an exception (e.g., due to database connection issues, validation at the store level, or other internal errors), the server will crash with an unhandled exception.

Consider wrapping this in try-catch:
```typescript
try {
  const todo = todoStore.create({ 
    title: title.trim(), 
    description: description?.trim() || undefined 
  });
  res.status(201).json(todo);
} catch (error) {
  res.status(500).json({
    error: 'Internal server error',
    details: [{ field: 'general', message: 'Failed to create todo' }]
  });
}
